<h2>Help</h2>
Most operations are self explanatory, especially with the help in the popup text.
Only the non-intuitive operations are described here:

<h3>Moving (reparenting) a keyword</h3>
Click on a keyword in the left pane to list its linked items in the middle pane. 
In the middle pane go to the keyword path printed at the top of the pane and 
grab the leaf (the part in bold) and drop it onto a new keyword on the left pane.
You may also drop it onto 'root' to make the keyword a root keyword.

<h3>Links between items</h3>
In the notes entry of a note or source you can make links to another note or
source. To make a link to another note, in the text field type
<code>[text to link][note:XXX]</code> where XXX is the note id. To make a link
to another source type <code>[source:citeykey]</code> where citekey is the
citekey of the source, like savitzky1964

<h3>Math text</h3>
RRiki uses Peter Jipsen's <a href="http://www1.chapman.edu/~jipsen/mathml/asciimath.html">ASCIIMathML</a> to convert latex strings to equations. Type 
"amath" in a field to activate the relevant javascript so that your text will
be displayed as math when you view it.

