<h2>Description</h2>
<p>RRiki is a program to store and organize information for, primarily, academic research. Such information includes citations for sources (articles,books etc), notes on sources and general notes. The latest version of RRiki can be downloaded from <a href="http://rriki.sf.net">rriki.sourceforge.net</a></p>

<h2>Author</h2>
<p>RRiki was developed by <a href="mailto:kghose@sf.net">Kaushik Ghose</a> who used it to procrastinate during his <a href="http://hdl.handle.net/1903/3397">PhD thesis</a> and even during his postdoc(s). Admittedly, RRiki and its precursor, <a href="http://r-a.sf.net">RA</a>, were vital for the writing of the thesis and subsequent papers.</p>

